        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Method 2: Exact Analytical for Dothan Model\n",
        "\n",
        "For the Dothan model, a semi-analytical formula exists. Using the discretized approximation:\n",
        "\n",
        "For a short time period $\\Delta t$, the bond price at the next step is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$P(t+\\Delta t, T) \\approx \\exp\\left( -r_t \\Delta t \\right) \\cdot E_t[P(t+\\Delta t, T)]$$\n",
        "\n",
        "This allows **exact** (to discretization error) pricing by working backward through the tree.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Comparison: Analytics vs. Simulation"
      ],
      "id": "200ddcf7"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| code-fold: true\n",
        "#| code-summary: \"Compare analytical vs simulated prices\"\n",
        "\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "\n",
        "# Dothan parameters\n",
        "r0 = 0.03\n",
        "mu = 0.02\n",
        "sigma = 0.15\n",
        "T_max = 10\n",
        "\n",
        "# Theoretical analysis for Dothan model\n",
        "# Under risk-neutral measure: bond price = exp(-r0 * (exp(mu_Q * T) - 1) / mu_Q)\n",
        "mu_Q = 0.0  # Risk-neutral drift (often set to 0)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Using simulation\n",
        "pricer = DothanBondPricer(r0=r0, mu=mu, sigma=sigma)\n",
        "maturities = [1, 3, 5, 7, 10]\n",
        "\n",
        "results = []\n",
        "for T in maturities:\n",
        "    sim_price, sim_std = pricer.price_bond(0, T, dt=0.01, n_paths=10000, seed=42)\n",
        "    \n",
        "    # Closed form for Dothan (risk-neutral)\n",
        "    # This is a simplification; exact formula is more complex\n",
        "    analytical_price = np.exp(-r0 * (np.exp(mu_Q * T) - 1) / max(mu_Q, 0.001))\n",
        "    \n",
        "    results.append({\n",
        "        'Maturity': T,\n",
        "        'Simulated': sim_price,\n",
        "        'Simulated Std': sim_std,\n",
        "        'Difference': abs(sim_price - analytical_price)\n",
        "    })\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.DataFrame(results)\n",
        "print(\"\\nComparison: Monte Carlo vs Analytical\")\n",
        "print(df.to_string(index=False))"
      ],
      "id": "21ff9f1a",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
